BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:🚀 Firefly Alpha Block 2 | INCUS [To Be Determined]
DTSTART:20261031T000000Z
DTEND:20261031T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260531T084213Z
UID:2944f240-launch@nasa-events-ics
DESCRIPTION:Provider: Firefly Aerospace\nLaunch site: Wallops Flight Facil
 ity\, Virginia\, USA\n\nThe Investigation of Convective Updrafts (INCUS) i
 s a NASA Earth science mission led by Colorado State University that will 
 investigate the behavior of tropical storms in order to better represent t
 hese storms in weather and climate models. It consists of 3 SmallSats flyi
 ng in tight coordination to study why convective storms\, heavy precipitat
 ion\, and clouds occur exactly when and where they form. \n\nEach satellit
 e will have a high frequency precipitation radar that observes rapid chang
 es in convective cloud depth and intensities. 1 of the 3 satellites also w
 ill carry a microwave radiometer to provide the spatial content of the lar
 ger scale weather observed by the radars. By flying so closely together\, 
 the satellites will use the slight differences in when they make observati
 ons to apply a novel time-differencing approach to estimate the vertical t
 ransport of convective mass.\n\nDetails: https://ll.thespacedevs.com/2.3.0
 /launches/c0dc723a-2322-4986-97d6-f64877aec846/?format=json
LOCATION:Wallops Flight Facility\, Virginia\, USA
URL:https://ll.thespacedevs.com/2.3.0/launches/c0dc723a-2322-4986-97d6-f64
 877aec846/?format=json
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:📡 Artemis III Crew Announcement
DTSTART:20260609T150000Z
DTEND:20260609T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260531T084213Z
UID:4afce7bd-event@nasa-events-ics
DESCRIPTION:Type: Press Event\n\nNASA will provide an update on the agency
 ’s Artemis III mission and announce the astronauts assigned to the test 
 flight.\n\nArtemis III will launch four astronauts from NASA’s Kennedy S
 pace Center in Florida aboard the Orion spacecraft on the SLS (Space Launc
 h System) rocket. The mission will test critical rendezvous and docking ca
 pabilities between Orion and commercial human landing systems needed to de
 liver astronauts to the lunar surface. Building on the successful Artemis 
 II crewed test flight in April\, Artemis III will pave the way for future 
 surface missions.\n\nDetails: https://ll.thespacedevs.com/2.3.0/events/148
 8/?format=json
URL:https://ll.thespacedevs.com/2.3.0/events/1488/?format=json
END:VEVENT
